  "prompt": "Epics of India: Is it true that peacocks don't mate physically?",
  "response": "No, it is not true that peacocks don't mate physically. Peacocks, like other birds, do engage in physical mating. The belief that they don't may stem from a misunderstanding or myth. In reality, the peacock performs a courtship display with its colorful tail feathers to attract the peahen, and if she is interested, they will mate physically. This myth might be confused with the idea that peacocks are associated with purity in some cultures, but this does not affect their actual mating behavior.",
